http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/FRAT-seeks-steps-to-establish-shipyard/article13995123.ece

The Federation of Residents’ Associations Thiruvananthapuram (FRAT) has urged the Central and State governments to adopt steps to establish the first deep-sea ship manufacturing unit of the country in Poovar as part of the Vizhinjan seaport project. In a statement, FRAT president Pattom Sasidharan Nair and general secretary M.S. Venugopal said that the proposal to establish the shipyard had immense potential with over one lakh vessels passing by along the international sea route every year. — Staff Reporter